Commentary Text: Chahal to Samson, out Caught&Bowled!! And he strikes first-ball! What a catch from Chahal! They're checking for a clean catch. Soft signal is OUT. Seemed alright in real time. Okay, the replays are quite confusing. It does seem like a bit of his fingers are under the ball, but also a portion of it seems to be touching the ground. The third umpire isn't sure but he feels there isn't enough evidence to overturn the onfield call. So, Samson has to walk. Huge, huge wicket this. Was doled out full by Chahal and Samson moved leg-side to drive through the covers. Got it off the inside part of the bat and the ball was travelling to the right of the bowler. Chahal stuck his right hand to pouch it. A very fine reflex attempt. RR in disarray here. Samson c and b Chahal 4(3) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Navdeep Saini to Buttler, out Caught by Devdutt Padikkal!! What a way to start your spell! This is a massive strike first-ball by Saini. The dangerous Buttler is out of here. The umpires wanted to refer it upstairs for a bump ball but Jos was already walking. He knew it was a fair dismissal. Raw pace probably did him in here, very full and outside off, Buttler tried to squeeze the drive but could only get a thick edge. Padikkal was placed at a wide slip, perhaps strategically and it's straight at him. Sharp low catch and RCB are absolutely pumped. Dream start for them. Buttler c Devdutt Padikkal b Navdeep Saini 22(12) [4s-3 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Shreyas Gopal to Finch, out Lbw!! It's that man again - Shreyas Gopal, who strikes for Rajasthan. He usually does well against RCB and has got a wicket in his first over. Flighted just outside off - the googly which spun back in - Finch was alerted by his partner about this threat, still he went low to sweep and failed to connect. The impact was in-line and the only question was whether it was hitting the stumps. Gopal was proved right and RCB have lost their first wicket. Finch lbw b Shreyas Gopal 8(7) [4s-2]
